Stir boiling water into dry gelatin mix in large serving bowl at least 2 min. until completely dissolved. Add ice cubes; stir until completely melted. Gently stir in 1-1/2 cups each of the whipped topping and strawberries until well blended. Spoon evenly into six small dessert dishes. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Top with remaining 1/2 cup each whipped topping and strawberries just before serving. Store leftovers in refrigerator.